The article is an editorial from The Wall Street Journal titled "It's time for Senators to stand up and confirm Brett Kavanaugh." The author argues that the Senate hearing on Brett Kavanaugh's Supreme Court nomination was an embarrassment and should have never happened. They believe that Kavanaugh's self-defense during the hearing was powerful and emotional, and that he has no history of the behavior he is accused of. The author criticizes Kavanaugh's opponents for their character assassination and argues that rejecting his nomination would bring dishonor to the Senate and validate smear politics. They call on Senators to confirm Kavanaugh.